Byte
0 1 2 3 Bits 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 0 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 T A B C 12 D The T field identifies the format and usage of A, B, C, and D as indicated below: T Description 00b OUI-Format

C&D 24 bit qualifier 01b EN - Format (IANA Enterprise Number)
A - Reserved
B&C EN (IANA Enterprise Number)
D - Qualifier 10b "Random"
A - Reserved
B&C Random
D - Qualifier 11b A,B,C&D Reserved For the T field values 00b and 01b, a combination of A and B (for 00b) or B and C (for 01b) identifies the vendor or organization whose component (software or hardware) generates this ISID.
